Class CalendarRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openntf.calendars.CalendarRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, CalendarRangeInterface

    public class CalendarRange
extends java.lang.Object
implements CalendarRangeInterface
    Carrier for a pair of two Calendar objects specifying a range of time.

      • validate

        public boolean validate()
        Validates the order of entries within this object. If a non-null entry exists for both the first and last entries, this method verifies that the first entry represents a moment in time NOT AFTER to that of the last entry. If the first entry represents a moment AFTER that of the last entry, this method swaps them.
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the Calendar range is Valid.
        See Also:
        isValid()

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Description copied from interface: CalendarRangeInterface
        Indicates if this CalendarRange object is valid. Rules for determing if a CalendarRange object is valid are as follows:
        • The First calendar object in the range must not be null
        • The Last calendar object in the range must not be null
        • The Last calendar object may not represent a date / time which is PRIOR to the First calendar object (they may be equal)
        Specified by:
        isValid in interface CalendarRangeInterface
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the CalendarRange object is valid

      • isInRange

        public boolean isInRange(java.lang.Object object)
        Description copied from interface: CalendarRangeInterface
        Tests a Calendar-Convertable Object to determine if it falls within the range of Calendar entries within this object. A Calendar-Convertable object is any object which can be converted to a Calendar. Returns false if the specifieds Object is null. Performs an inclusive test, returns true if the specified Object is equal to either the first or last entry.
        Specified by:
        isInRange in interface CalendarRangeInterface
        Parameters:
        object - Object to test
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the Object falls within this object's range.

      • getIntersection

        public CalendarRange getIntersection(CalendarRange cr)

        Tests a CalendarRange object to determine if there is an intersection with this object's Range. Note this tests the RANGE encompassed by this object, not just specific entry instances. NOTE both objects MUST be valid (non-null values for first and last entries) Performs an inclusive test, the first and last entries included.
